In $\triangle ABC$, the sides opposite to angles $A$, $B$, and $C$ are $a$, $b$, and $c$ respectively, and $\sin \frac{B}{2}-\cos \frac{B}{2}= \frac{1}{5}$.

(I) Find the value of $\cos B$;

